Dave,

yes, you&#39;re right &#39;bulk&#39; was the wrong word, what I mean was the pure
species viscosity and thermal conductivity. Sorry for that. 

The difference between getViscosities and getSpeciesViscosities is
that I get an error &#39;class Cantera::Transport&#39; has no member named
&#39;getSpeciesViscosities&#39; when I use getSpeciesViscosities. I think this
could be a compiler problem (mingw-gcc 3.3/3.4). That&#39;s why and also
because I needed pure species thermal conductivities I made these two
functions, which was originally thought for my use only.

ulf


