&gt; --- In cantera@yahoogroups.com, &quot;usenechal&quot; &lt;senechal@t...&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Hello all,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; to get an answer to my own question on getting bulk viscosities I
&gt; made
&gt; &gt; some modification on the cantera-sourcecode. 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I modified mixtransport.h and inserted:
&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt;         virtual void getViscosities(doublereal* sv);
&gt; &gt;         virtual void getConductivities(doublereal* tc);
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; between getSpeciesViscosities and getBinaryDiffCoeffs. 
&gt; &gt; And mixtransport.cpp by inserting:
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt;     void MixTransport::getViscosities(doublereal* sv) {
&gt; &gt;         update_T();
&gt; &gt;         update_C();
&gt; &gt; 	updateSpeciesViscosities();
&gt; &gt;         int k;
&gt; &gt; 	for (k = 0; k &lt; m_nsp; k++) {
&gt; &gt; 	   sv[k]=m_visc[k];
&gt; &gt; 	}
&gt; &gt;     }
&gt; &gt;     void MixTransport::getConductivities(doublereal* tc) {
&gt; &gt;         update_T();
&gt; &gt;         update_C();
&gt; &gt;         if (!m_spcond_ok)  updateCond_T(); 
&gt; &gt;         if (!m_condmix_ok) {
&gt; &gt;         	int k;
&gt; &gt; 		for (k = 0; k &lt; m_nsp; k++) {
&gt; &gt; 	   	tc[k]=m_cond[k];
&gt; &gt; 	   	}
&gt; &gt; 	}
&gt; &gt;     }
&gt; &gt; Between MixTransport::getSpeciesFluxes and MixTr
&gt; ansport::getMixDiffCoeffs.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; With theese modifications I recompiled cantera and can now do
&gt; &gt; something like this:
&gt; &gt;    Transport *tran = newTransportMgr(&quot;Mix&quot;, gas);
&gt; &gt;    double visc[kk];
&gt; &gt;    double cond[kk];
&gt; &gt;    tran-&gt;getViscosities(visc);
&gt; &gt;    tran-&gt;getConductivities(cond);
&gt; &gt; In visc[i] and cond[i] are then the viscosities and thermal
&gt; &gt; conductivities...
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I find this very useful and want to ask if it is possible to include
&gt; &gt; these modifications into the official cantera source ?
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Best regards,
&gt; &gt; Ulf
